race.description: Tabtouch Place A Same Race Multi Maiden
race.comment: JUST PETTY CASH (12) settled handy on debut at Northam when beaten 1L before going for a spell. She's trialled nicely either side of the debut run and has switched to the Nash stable since. Maps for a lovely run in transit here and she looks beautifully placed to get the job done. GOOD SHOW (7) is a gelding on debut for the Grantham stable with two trials under his belt coming into this. Parnham hops on board despite not trialling the gelding, who is out of G1 placegetter Enticing Star. Should get his chance in what looks a suitable race on debut. ALL OUR FAITH (11) is another debutant who seems to be relishing life for the new stable up in Geraldton. While there's no doubt been issues in her early career, her recent trial was solid enough to suggest she can run a cheeky race. LOONA DAWN (10) has had a few goes now but is knocking on the door. COSTA STAR (9) is next best.
